This paper discusses a consistency model for distributed data stores, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper specifically focuses on the implementation of the GentleRain protocol, which is a data store protocol, and thus could also fall under the category of Databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of physical clocks and Hybrid Logical Clocks, which are relevant to Operating Systems (cs.OS) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the protocol, which could also fall under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
